1.q_string: The weight percentage of \(\mathrm{NaCl}\) solution is 10 . If the weight of the solution is \(150 \mathrm{gms}\), then calculate the weight of \(\mathrm{Na}\) and water in gms.

\(5 \mathrm{~g}\) of crystalline salt, when rendered anhydrous, lost \(1.89 \mathrm{~g}\) of water. The formula weight of anhydrous salts is 160 . The number of molecules of water of crystallisation in the salt is:

\(\mathrm{Cu}_{2} \mathrm{~S}\) and \(\mathrm{M}_{2} \mathrm{~S}\) are isomorphous in which percentage of sulphur is \(20.14 \%\) and \(12.94 \%\) respectively. The atomic weight of \(M\) is:

[Atomic wt. of \(\mathrm{Cu}=63.5]\)
A 1.24 M aqueous solution of KI has density of \(1.15 \mathrm{~g} / \mathrm{cm}^{3}\). What is the percentage composition of solute in the solution?

\(60 \mathrm{ml}\) of a mixture of nitrous oxide and nitric oxide was exploded with excess of hydrogen. If \(38 \mathrm{ml}\) of \(\mathrm{N}_{2}\) was formed, calculate the volume of each gas in the mixture.

4 When \(100 \mathrm{ml}\) of a \(\mathrm{O}_{2}-\mathrm{O}_{3}\) mixture was passed through turpentine, there was the reduction of volume by \(20 \mathrm{ml}\). If \(100 \mathrm{ml}\) of such a mixture is heated, what will be the increase in volume?

When a certain quantity of oxygen was ozonised in suitable apparatus, the volume decreased by \(4 \mathrm{~m}\). On addition of turpentine the volume further decreased by \(8 \mathrm{ml}\). All volumes were measured at the same temperature and pressure. From these data, establish the formula of ozone.

\(15 \mathrm{~g}\) of methyl alcohol is present in \(100 \mathrm{ml}\) of solution. If density of solution is \(0.90 \mathrm{~g} / \mathrm{ml}\). Calculate the mass percentage of methyl alcohol in solution.

\(300 \mathrm{~g}\) of an aqueous solution of a particular solute (containing 30 \% solute by mass) is mixed with \(400 \mathrm{~g}\) of another aqueous solution of the same solute (containing \(40 \%\) solute by mass). In the final solution, mass \(\%\) of solute is :

[Given, Molecular mass of solute = 50]
The mole fraction of solute in aqueous urea solution is 0.2. The mass percent of solute is:

q_option: The total mass of reactants \(=\) Total mass of the products. It follows the law of conservation of mass.
The total mass of reactants \(=\) Total mass of the products. Therefore, the law of multiple proportions is followed.
Amount of \(\mathrm{Fe}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{3}\) can be increased by taking any one of the reactants (iron or oxygen) in excess.
Amount of \(\mathrm{Fe}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{3}\) produced will decrease if the amount of any one of the reactants (iron or oxygen) is taken in excess.
1.q_string:
Which of the following statements is correct about the reaction given below?

\(4 \mathrm{Fe}(\mathrm{s})+3 \mathrm{O}_{2}(\mathrm{~g}) \rightarrow 2 \mathrm{Fe}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{3}(\mathrm{~g})\)

The vapours of organic compound was burnt in oxygen. Equal volume of both gaseous substance were taken at same pressure and temperature. After the reaction, the system was returned to the original condition and it turn out that its volume has not changed. The product of combustion contain \(50 \% \mathrm{CO}_{2}(\mathrm{~g})\) and \(50 \% \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}(\mathrm{g})\) by volume and no other gas. Find the molecular weight of organic compound (in gram \(/ \mathrm{mol}\) ) in question.

\(10 \mathrm{ml}\) of \(\mathrm{CO}\) is mixed with \(25 \mathrm{ml}\) air having 20 per cent \(\mathrm{O}_{2}\) by volume. What would be the final volume if none of \(\mathrm{CO}\) and \(\mathrm{O}_{2}\) is left after the reaction?

\(40 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{Ba}\left(\mathrm{MnO}_{4}\right)_{2}\) (mol. wt. \(\left.=375 \mathrm{~g} / \mathrm{mol}\right)\) sample containing some inert impurities in acidic medium is completely reacted with \(125 \mathrm{~mL}\) of \(33.6 \mathrm{~V}\) of \(\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{2}\). What is the percentage purity of the sample?
